The paper deals with machine translation evaluation using neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also extensively uses neural networks for modeling and prediction, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional and recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (CV) and sequential data processing, respectively, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV possible sub-categories.
